        "metrics": ["Pearson correlation between condition number and per-head accuracy drop", "Effective rank distribution across heads", "Spectral radius variance quantification (95% CI)"]
      },
      {
        "name": "Precision Routing via Spectral Thresholding",
        "description": "Implement deterministic routing: allocate head h to precision tier based on diagnostic thresholds: (1) κ(Q^T K) > τ_high → FP32; κ(Q^T K) ∈ [τ_mid, τ_high] → FP16; κ(Q^T K) < τ_mid → INT8. Set thresholds via cross-validation on GLUE dev (optimize for accuracy-speedup Pareto front). Thresholds are model-specific but dataset-agnostic. Enforce block-level tiering: all heads in a block share precision to guarantee <2% inference overhead. Compare against: (a) uniform INT8, (b) uniform FP16, (c) layer-wise quantization (quantize all heads in layer uniformly), (d) magnitude-based pruning (prune heads with smallest norms).",
        "metrics": ["Model accuracy on GLUE, SQuAD, WikiText perplexity", "Inference latency (FLOPs, actual wall-clock on single GPU)", "Speedup relative to FP32 baseline", "Amortized diagnostic overhead (% of inference time)"]
      },
      {
        "name": "PAC-Bayes Generalization Bound Verification",
        "description": "For each head, derive PAC-Bayes generalization bound under quantization: bound_h = empirical_loss_h + O(√(log(1/δ) * KL(posterior || prior)) / m), where KL term depends on Hessian conditioning. Derive prior as isotropic Gaussian with variance scaled by 1/κ(H_h) (ill-conditioned heads require sharper priors). For each precision tier, compute empirical loss on calibration set and theoretical bound. Verify: (1) bound holds on held-out test set; (2) bounds correctly rank heads by precision sensitivity (heads with larger bounds should be assigned higher precision); (3) bounds are tight (ratio of bound to actual test error < 5).",
        "metrics": ["Bound violation rate (% of heads where test error > PAC-Bayes bound)", "Tightness ratio: max(bound / test_error) across heads", "Correlation between bound magnitude and assigned precision tier"]
      },
      {
        "name": "Perturbation Error Analysis and Stability Radii",
        "description": "Formally quantify numerical stability under precision switching. For each head, model quantization as additive perturbation: Q̃ = Q + ΔQ where ||ΔQ|| ≤ ε_quant (derived from INT8 range). Bound output perturbation via: ||softmax(Q̃^T K̃)Ṽ - softmax(Q^T K)V|| ≤ f(κ(Q^T K), ε_quant). Compute stability radius: maximum ε_quant that keeps output perturbation < 0.1% of activation norm. Verify: (1) stability radius correlates with spectral condition number (higher κ → smaller stability radius); (2) heads assigned INT8 have stability radius > measured INT8 error; (3) stability radius estimates are conservative (actual error < predicted bound with 95% confidence across 10 seeds).",
        "metrics": ["Stability radius per head (mm. ε_quant)", "Ratio of stability radius to actual INT8 quantization error", "Perturbation bound violation rate on held-out batches"]
      },
