        "name": "Ablation: Diagnostic Component Importance",
        "description": "Isolate contribution of each spectral diagnostic: (1) routing based only on κ(Q^T K); (2) routing based only on singular value decay (effective rank); (3) routing based only on gradient covariance spectral radius; (4) full SCR (all three). For each variant, measure accuracy-speedup Pareto front on GLUE tasks. Expected: combined diagnostics outperform any single metric, with diminishing returns after including top-2 metrics.",
        "metrics": ["Accuracy drop vs. speedup for each variant", "Computational cost of each diagnostic component"]
      },
