        "name": "Generalization Across Tasks and Model Sizes",
        "description": "Train diagnostic thresholds on GLUE (SST-2, MNLI, QQP). Evaluate on held-out tasks: SQuAD (QA), WikiText (language modeling), CIFAR-10 (vision-language model, if applicable). Also test on model variants: BERT-small, BERT-large, GPT-2-small, GPT-2-medium, LLaMA-7B, LLaMA-13B. Expected: thresholds derived from GLUE generalize with <1% accuracy loss to new tasks; scaling laws hold across model sizes (condition number distributions shift predictably).",
