        "name": "Variance and Reproducibility Analysis",
        "description": "Run all experiments with 10 random seeds (different calibration batches, initialization for power iteration). Compute 95% confidence intervals for all metrics. Verify: (1) spectral diagnostics are stable across seeds (CI < 5% of mean); (2) precision routing decisions are deterministic given calibration batch; (3) accuracy variance is well-characterized (no silent failures).",
