      "**Calibration Batch Dependency**: Spectral diagnostics depend on representative calibration data. If calibration distribution differs from deployment, routing decisions may be suboptimal. Mitigation: validate generalization across diverse tasks (Exp. 6); characterize sensitivity to calibration set size.",
      "**Overhead of Spectral Computation**: SVD and power iteration incur computational cost. Risk: diagnostic overhead exceeds speedup gains for small models. Mitigation: enforce <5% overhead budget; use fast SVD approximations (randomized SVD); amortize over multiple inference batches.",
      "**Threshold Sensitivity**: PAC-Bayes thresholds τ_high, τ_mid are hyperparameters. Risk: small threshold variations cause large precision tier changes. Mitigation: perform sensitivity analysis; use confidence intervals to set conservative thresholds; validate stability across tasks (Exp. 5).",
      "**Limited to Attention Layers**: Framework targets attention subspaces; does not address FFN or embedding precision. Mitigation: extend diagnostics to FFN (similar spectral analysis of weight matrices) in future work; current scope is well-defined and achieves meaningful speedups.",
      "**PAC-Bayes Bound Looseness**: Theoretical bounds may be loose, reducing practical utility for threshold setting. Mitigation: empirically validate bound tightness (Exp. 3); use empirical risk as primary routing signal with bounds as guardrails.",
      "**Single-GPU Deployment Constraint**: Framework assumes single GPU; multi-GPU mixed-precision strategies may require different routing. Mitigation: focus on single-GPU regime (aligns with micro-grant constraints); document scalability assumptions clearly.",
      "**Precision Tier Discretization**: Coarse-grained tiering (FP32, FP16, INT8) may miss fine-grained optimal allocations. Risk: suboptimal Pareto front compared to per-head precision. Mitigation: justify tiering choice via overhead analysis; show diminishing returns of finer granularity.",
      "**Generalization to New Architectures**: Diagnostics are designed for standard transformers (Q, K, V projections). Risk: may not transfer to novel architectures (mixture-of-experts, multi-query attention). Mitigation: clearly document architectural assumptions; provide extension guidelines."
    ]
  }
}

